### Confidence Levels

| Level | Definition | Standard |
|-------|------------|----------|
| **High** | Well-established | 2+ Tier 1â€“2 sources OR 1 unambiguous Tier 1 |
| **Medium** | Likely accurate, some uncertainty | 1 Tier 1â€“2 OR multiple Tier 3 in agreement |
| **Low** | Plausible, significant uncertainty | Tier 3â€“4 only, limited corroboration |
| **Speculative** | Cannot assess | Noted in Appendix C; no confident claim |

### Inference Rule
Label speculative implications with `[INFERENCE]`. Keep minimal and clearly justified.

